  "info": {
    "title": "Password Policy",
    "description": "**Below is detail each field for Password Policy**\n\n| Field                | Type    | Format | Description                                                     |\n|----------------------|---------|--------|-----------------------------------------------------------------|\n| name                 | string  |        | The name of the Standard User.                                  |\n| minimumLength        | integer |        | The minimum number of characters required for the user password.|\n| complexity           | integer |        | The level of password complexity required for the user password. It is represented by an integer value. Complexity Levels: 1 (Low Complexity), 2 (Medium Complexity), 3 (High Complexity). |\n| expiration           | integer |        | The number of days after which the user password will expire and require a change. |\n| minimumDuration      | integer |        | The minimum number of days for which a user must keep a password before being allowed to change it again. |\n| accountLockout       | integer |        | The maximum number of failed login attempts allowed before the user account gets locked out. |\n| accountLockoutDuration | integer |      | The duration (in minutes) for which a user account remains locked after reaching the maximum number of failed login attempts. |\n| passwordHistory      | integer |        | The number of previous passwords that the system will remember to prevent users from reusing them. |\n",
    "version": "1.0.0"
  },
