        "summary": "Read Password Policies",
        "tags":["Password Policy"],
        "description": "**Below is the detail for each field of the Password Policy:**\n\n| Field                  | Type    | Format | Description                                                                                                                                                                                            |\n| ---------------------- | ------- | ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n| name                   | string  |        | The name of the Standard User.                                                                                                                                                                         |\n| minimumLength          | integer |        | The minimum number of characters required for the user password. *Min: 6*                                                                                                                              |\n| complexity             | integer |        | The level of password complexity required for the user password. It is represented by an integer value. Complexity Levels: (Low Complexity), (Medium Complexity), (High Complexity). *Min:1* & *Max:4* |\n| expiration             | integer |        | The number of days after which the user password will expire and require a change. <br> if value is *-1* this is for **Never expiration**                                                                                                                  |\n| minimumDuration        | integer |        | The minimum number of days for which a user must keep a password before being allowed to change it again. <br> if value is *-1* this is for **Never**                                                                                             |\n| accountLockout         | integer |        | The maximum number of failed login attempts allowed before the user account gets locked out.                                                                                                           |\n| accountLockoutDuration | integer |        | The duration (in minutes) for which a user account remains locked after reaching the maximum number of failed login attempts. <br> if value is *-1* this is for **Account locked out forever**                                                                          |\n| passwordHistory        | integer |        | The number of previous passwords that the system will remember to prevent users from reusing them.                                                                                                     |",
        "produces": ["application/json"],
